description: The SPDR S&P Insurance ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Insurance Select Industry Index (the “Index”)Seeks to provide exposure to the insurance segment of the S&P TMI, which comprises the following sub-industries: Insurance Brokers, Life & Health Insurance, Multi-Line Insurance, Property & Casualty Insurance, and ReinsuranceSeeks to track a modified equal weighted index which provides the potential for unconcentrated industry exposure across large, mid and small cap stocksAllows investors to take strategic or tactical positions at a more targeted level than traditional sector based investing
name: SPDR S&P Insurance ETF
